00:51:06,560 --> 00:51:08,710
But it's very rare, I must say.

739
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:10,758
OK, then.

740
00:51:11,840 --> 00:51:15,435
So you give them the address
and they can knock on my door anytime?

741
00:51:17,720 --> 00:51:20,188
No, we'll call you first.

742
00:51:25,640 --> 00:51:28,598
Your gesture does you proud, sir.

743
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:31,080
You will be giving back hope to a family
that is suffering.

744
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:32,599
On their behalf, I thank you!

745
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:35,590
The nurse will give you
everything you need.

746
00:51:37,920 --> 00:51:40,229
And... the money?

747
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:43,153
In 2 or 3 days, once we've done our tests.

748
00:51:43,440 --> 00:51:46,079
Don't worry, the nurse will guide you.

749
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:47,474
- Thank you.
- You're welcome!

750
00:51:47,680 --> 00:51:48,715
Bye.

751
00:51:55,760 --> 00:51:57,273
- Petrescu!
- Yes!

752
00:51:57,480 --> 00:51:58,708
Come with me.

753
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:08,233
Is everything alright?

754
00:52:08,800 --> 00:52:12,315
Excuse me, do you have a magazine
or something?

755
00:52:53,320 --> 00:52:54,992
My name is Manuela.

756
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:57,191
My name is Manuela.

757
00:52:59,280 --> 00:53:01,316
I'm 30 years old.

758
00:53:01,960 --> 00:53:03,916
I like you a lot.

759
00:53:04,680 --> 00:53:07,638
You like me... a lot?

760
00:53:07,840 --> 00:53:10,798
I like you a lot.

761
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:15,750
No, no.
French lessons.

762
00:53:16,000 --> 00:53:17,672
OK, OK.

763
00:53:20,600 --> 00:53:22,511
Do you want to come to France with me?

764
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:25,111
Come to France with me.

765
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:33,160
No, I work at the factory.

766
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:38,712
What are you going to do
when they close down the factory?

767
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:42,560
I work at the factory.

768
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:46,638
No. You can't.

769
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:52,750
Yes, yes. I work at the factory.
300 workers.

770
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:54,712
- You can't.
- Why?

771
00:53:54,920 --> 00:53:57,195
Because there will be no factory.

772
00:53:57,440 --> 00:53:59,271
It will close for good.

773
00:53:59,600 --> 00:54:01,716
We will sell all the
equipment and that's it.

774
00:54:03,680 --> 00:54:05,591
No one needs your factory.

775
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:08,312
They don't care.

776
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:12,438
This place is dead.

777
00:54:15,240 --> 00:54:17,674
But you said that 300 workers...

778
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:18,915
It's a lie.

779
00:54:21,240 --> 00:54:23,356
No one cares about you people.

780
00:54:25,080 --> 00:54:29,710
We won't make snail cans there.
We'll sell everything and that's it.

781
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:33,073
But I care about what happens to you.

782
00:54:33,440 --> 00:54:34,998
Manuela...

783
00:54:36,880 --> 00:54:38,677
Come to France with me.

784
00:54:40,200 --> 00:54:42,316
Here you have no future.

785
00:54:45,520 --> 00:54:46,714
You came all this way,

786
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:50,515
you lied to us and now
you're telling me to go with you to France?

787
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:53,678
Yes, because I tell you the truth.

788
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:55,831
Yes, yes, the truth.

789
00:56:49,320 --> 00:56:50,992
- Mama...
- Yes.

790
00:56:51,240 --> 00:56:52,912
Do you think daddy is OK?

791
00:56:53,640 --> 00:56:55,119
Yes, I think so.

792
00:56:55,520 --> 00:56:58,080
Do you think he wrote to
the Sultan of Brunei?

793
00:56:58,720 --> 00:57:00,631
I don't know. Why are you asking?

794
00:57:01,320 --> 00:57:03,072
For the bicycle.

795
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:04,909
I don't know...

796
00:57:08,680 --> 00:57:11,478
Mama, are you also afraid at night?

797
00:57:12,640 --> 00:57:14,710
Come on, enough, go to sleep.
Good night!

798
00:57:14,920 --> 00:57:16,035
Good night.

799
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:40,631
They want more.

800
00:57:40,840 --> 00:57:42,990
The Prime Minister's signature,

801
00:57:43,720 --> 00:57:45,756
the Economic Advisor's signature,

802
00:57:45,960 --> 00:57:50,238
the Minister of Finance's signature.
It's not that easy.

803
00:57:50,520 --> 00:57:53,910
You sell the equipment for a high price...

804
00:57:54,160 --> 00:57:57,040
I'm selling it for a high price,
but we're partners, we split the profit.

805
00:57:57,200 --> 00:57:58,838
Fifty-fifty.

806
00:57:58,960 --> 00:58:01,349
Yes, I understand.

807
00:58:02,240 --> 00:58:04,800
I have many risks... The workers.

808
00:58:06,680 --> 00:58:08,557
Press everywhere.

809
00:58:09,520 --> 00:58:11,715
200... 200.

810
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:25,952
The visit to the foster home
was divided in 2 parts.

811
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:31,911
One private, in which Michael found out
that our kids know how to sing,

812
00:58:32,200 --> 00:58:36,955
he received a gift from them
and generously offered autographs.

813
00:58:38,320 --> 00:58:41,357
Then the star went to the kids' playground,

814
00:58:41,560 --> 00:58:44,393
built by the Heal the World Foundation.

815
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:46,836
Michael's love for the children...

816
00:58:54,840 --> 00:58:56,068
Hello!

817
00:58:57,360 --> 00:58:58,759
Ana, is that you?

818
00:59:14,120 --> 00:59:15,348
Ana...

819
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:18,992
I'm sorry!

820
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:24,236
I tried to do something
to make things better for us.

821
00:59:25,120 --> 00:59:26,155
But..

822
00:59:28,360 --> 00:59:29,918
I don't know...

823
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:35,153
I didn't think
you would leave over this.

824
00:59:38,840 --> 00:59:41,229
Now I don't know what to do.

825
00:59:51,080 --> 00:59:52,957
Is Viorel OK?

826
00:59:55,400 --> 00:59:58,472
Ana... come back home!

827
01:00:00,440 --> 01:00:02,192
I love you!

828
01:00:04,720 --> 01:00:07,553
George, it's me.

829
01:00:10,000 --> 01:00:12,560
Listen... be careful.
These guys are out to trick you.

830
01:00:18,720 --> 01:00:21,598
- What?
- They won 't take anybody back.

831
01:00:21,800 --> 01:00:25,588
This story with 300 people is a lie.
They're closing the factory and that's it.

832
01:00:26,320 --> 01:00:27,833
But how do you know?

833
01:00:29,120 --> 01:00:30,599
Somebody told me.

834
01:00:31,680 --> 01:00:33,033
Who?

835
01:00:33,440 --> 01:00:36,113
Listen, tell everyone.
Everybody should know.

836
01:01:05,000 --> 01:01:07,036
- Did you sleep well?
- Great.

837
01:01:07,960 --> 01:01:11,316
I opened the window...
Fresh Romanian air.

838
01:01:12,640 --> 01:01:15,837
I' m really hung ry.
Shall we have breakfast?

839
01:01:16,160 --> 01:01:17,673
I already ate.

840
01:01:20,000 --> 01:01:21,274
Enjoy your meal!

841
01:01:24,080 --> 01:01:26,469
Stop pushing.
We' re registering all of you.

842
01:01:26,680 --> 01:01:29,877
Not you, Vasile.
Under 45 years, I told you.

843
01:01:33,520 --> 01:01:37,798
Ion, put out that cigarette. I told you.
You know you' re not allowed.

844
01:01:38,600 --> 01:01:41,273
Fill in this form here. Starting today,
no more drinking, no more smoking,

845
01:01:41,520 --> 01:01:43,317
and no touching your wife, understand?

846
01:01:43,560 --> 01:01:45,949
- And what if she wants to...?
- Say you have a headache.

847
01:01:46,280 --> 01:01:48,316
Come on, play the Bond.

848
01:01:48,920 --> 01:01:50,558
Better drop the gun.

849
01:01:50,960 --> 01:01:55,829
- Hey, Gica, how do we do it?
- How do we do what?

850
01:01:56,040 --> 01:01:58,241
Tomorrow we meet at the station
and leave for Bucharest.

851
01:01:58,440 --> 01:02:01,716
- No, man, how do we do that?
- What's that?

852
01:02:01,960 --> 01:02:04,155
That... thing... how do they collect it?

853
01:02:04,360 --> 01:02:06,440
They don't collect it themselves,
we give it to them.

854
01:02:06,560 --> 01:02:07,913
Just like that? No helping hand?

855
01:02:08,120 --> 01:02:10,841
Come on. I'll explain later.
See how many people are waiting in line?

856
01:02:10,960 --> 01:02:13,633
No shoving!
Have some patience, OK?

857
01:02:14,280 --> 01:02:14,917
How are you?

858
01:02:15,080 --> 01:02:15,751
Hi!

859
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:19,390
My brother-in-law saw a clinic
like that in China, on TV.

860
01:02:19,600 --> 01:02:22,319
And they had some nurses
helping the men.

861
01:02:22,520 --> 01:02:23,999
What, did they show
the nurses helping them?

862
01:02:24,200 --> 01:02:25,713
No, but I thought that's
why they were there.

863
01:02:25,920 --> 01:02:28,480
- Do they have nurses at this clinic?
- They do.

864
01:02:28,720 --> 01:02:30,119
Then let's...

865
01:02:30,560 --> 01:02:32,312
You should come, too!

866
01:02:32,560 --> 01:02:34,480
But when you were there,
did they help you a bit?

867
01:02:34,520 --> 01:02:35,919
Come on, I don't need that.

868
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:37,314
OK, whatever.

869
01:02:37,560 --> 01:02:41,269
- What do you think about this situation?
- The situation is like this.

870
01:02:41,560 --> 01:02:45,155
We realized that this way we can get
enough money to buy the plant.

871
01:02:45,440 --> 01:02:48,796
Pay off the debts, buy
a license for the new engine...

872
01:02:49,480 --> 01:02:51,436
and start production again.

873
01:02:51,680 --> 01:02:55,912
Until now we have a list with 250,
but we hope to have more volunteers.

874
01:02:56,200 --> 01:02:59,795
What are your arguments for this initiative
and what are your strong points?

875
01:03:00,800 --> 01:03:04,759
Well, here in our factory, we have
vigorous, strong, smart people.

876
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:08,037
What woman wouldn't want
a father like that for her child?

877
01:03:10,040 --> 01:03:12,873
We are determined to do this,
and please let everybody know.

878
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:16,789
Maybe a convenient solution can be found.
Or we'll go to Bucharest...

879
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:20,390
or maybe the clinic will open
a department here, in Campulung.

880
01:03:20,600 --> 01:03:23,717
Don't you think this might cause
trouble back home?

881
01:03:26,320 --> 01:03:29,153
Each of us should decide it
within their family.

882
01:03:29,360 --> 01:03:32,113
Or maybe individually.

883
01:03:32,920 --> 01:03:35,957
But I believe we shouldn't
get to this point.

884
01:03:36,280 --> 01:03:38,919
To go to such desperate measures.

885
01:03:40,600 --> 01:03:43,910
There is no problem.
Everything is under control.

886
01:03:45,920 --> 01:03:49,799
The French part is settled.

887
01:03:50,280 --> 01:03:52,510
But these guys have gone mad.

888
01:03:53,840 --> 01:03:58,152
Petrescu from the union, he's getting
them to think they can buy the plant.

889
01:04:00,040 --> 01:04:04,591
I'll take care of it! I'll take care of it.
Yes. It's OK.

890
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:10,994
Like... Iike we said.
Bye.

891
01:04:14,800 --> 01:04:16,682
Miss, I have my husband
and my son working

892
01:04:16,695 --> 01:04:18,588
here in this factory. I
don't agree with that.

893
01:04:18,880 --> 01:04:19,835
Go home.

894
01:04:20,240 --> 01:04:22,754
This is not normal.
Catalin, why do you...?

895
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:25,874
Go home, you're embarassing us.

896
01:04:28,240 --> 01:04:31,357
You think, just because we're poor,
we should sell just anything?

897
01:04:31,680 --> 01:04:33,272
The French are here!

898
01:04:49,360 --> 01:04:52,477
I think it's enough for me.
I'm out of here.

899
01:04:52,680 --> 01:04:55,797
Wait a second, what's going on?
What's wrong with you?

900
01:04:56,000 --> 01:04:58,719
We're almost done.
It's good. Everything was solved.

901
01:04:59,760 --> 01:05:01,591
We' re a team, aren't we?

902
01:05:01,800 --> 01:05:04,360
I don't like this game, Dad.
It's not fun.

903
01:05:04,560 --> 01:05:07,950
I came to help you...
That's it. I don't want to live like that.

904
01:05:09,120 --> 01:05:11,156
Olivier, this is not the moment.

905
01:05:11,640 --> 01:05:14,632
You know you can't save the world.

906
01:05:21,640 --> 01:05:25,315
We know that we're in a
diffiicult situation.

907
01:05:25,880 --> 01:05:29,190
We will make all efforts to fiind...

908
01:05:29,920 --> 01:05:31,956
It's a business that has to go well.

909
01:05:32,240 --> 01:05:35,312
If not, I'm fiinished.
It might be the last one.

910
01:05:36,200 --> 01:05:38,361
They will fiind a way, you'll see.
They' re used to it.

911
01:05:38,520 --> 01:05:41,080
They've always been knee-deep in shit.
I haven't.

912
01:05:46,040 --> 01:05:49,271
- OK. I understand.
- What?

913
01:05:51,040 --> 01:05:54,476
If you want to keep her, you have
to keep doing business like that.

914
01:05:54,720 --> 01:05:56,631
That's easy to see.

915
01:05:58,120 --> 01:06:01,795
OK, I'll let you do your business
with the parrot. I'm going.

916
01:06:18,200 --> 01:06:21,988
Nelu, let go of that cigarette.
You'll get sick.

917
01:06:39,400 --> 01:06:40,799
Good night!

918
01:06:41,400 --> 01:06:42,833
Good night.

919
01:06:45,080 --> 01:06:46,559
Are you tired?

920
01:06:47,600 --> 01:06:48,874
Are you tired?

921
01:06:49,040 --> 01:06:50,951
No, but you know tomorrow I'm going
to Bucharest with the guys.

922
01:06:51,080 --> 01:06:52,798
I know, I know...

923
01:06:53,320 --> 01:06:54,639
OK, good night.

924
01:06:55,000 --> 01:06:57,036
No... stop it!
Wait, wait!

925
01:06:57,240 --> 01:06:59,708
You know I can't. Wait!

926
01:06:59,920 --> 01:07:01,672
Come on, you know that.

927
01:07:01,880 --> 01:07:04,030
It was spelled out on the goddamn form!

928
01:07:04,240 --> 01:07:07,357
Yes, I know, but just a little.
They won't notice it.

929
01:07:08,120 --> 01:07:10,350
I can't, don't you understand?

930
01:07:12,080 --> 01:07:14,548
Woman, we have to save the plant.
What the hell?

931
01:07:14,840 --> 01:07:16,478
You don't love me anymore!

932
01:07:19,040 --> 01:07:22,032
I do love you. But I can't do it tonight.

933
01:07:22,840 --> 01:07:24,478
I' m working for export.

934
01:07:25,120 --> 01:07:26,519
Good night.

935
01:07:53,920 --> 01:07:59,074
I will forget everything I've had

936
01:08:02,760 --> 01:08:08,153
The burden I've carried so long,
The moment we said goodbye.

937
01:08:11,640 --> 01:08:17,033
I won't ask for the impossible
I won't ask for your love

938
01:08:23,960 --> 01:08:27,032
No need to look away

939
01:08:29,680 --> 01:08:36,119
Our paths might cross someday

940
01:08:38,480 --> 01:08:45,591
Our paths and love,
Our thoughts and happiness...

941
01:09:20,160 --> 01:09:22,754
Stop eating, man.

942
01:09:28,720 --> 01:09:31,393
Stop smoking. I told you.

943
01:09:33,160 --> 01:09:35,355
Who's sneaking in the front of the line?

944
01:09:35,680 --> 01:09:37,716
What's the hurry?

945
01:09:39,600 --> 01:09:41,955
- What's for sale here?
- Concert tickets.

946
01:09:42,120 --> 01:09:44,156
For Michael Jackson, free.

947
01:09:44,360 --> 01:09:46,316
- Who?
- Michael Jackson.

948
01:09:48,000 --> 01:09:50,594
Do you think you've got enough
cups for everybody?

949
01:09:50,800 --> 01:09:51,994
It's not possible to...

950
01:09:52,160 --> 01:09:54,594
We can come tomorrow as well.
In smaller groups.

951
01:09:54,800 --> 01:09:56,347
Still, we need to hurry
because the factory

952
01:09:56,360 --> 01:09:57,917
is going to be sold at
the end of the month.

953
01:09:58,080 --> 01:09:59,911
- Sir, that's not possible.
- Why not?

954
01:10:00,080 --> 01:10:01,308
Come on, Gica!

955
01:10:02,240 --> 01:10:05,640
I understand, you know. We're talking large
quantities here. Can I make a proposition?

956
01:10:05,840 --> 01:10:06,670
Sir...

957
01:10:06,880 --> 01:10:08,996
We can give you a discount.
Let's say 20 percent.

958
01:10:09,200 --> 01:10:10,349
That's enough, sir!

959
01:10:10,560 --> 01:10:12,198
This way you only pay 40 dollars
per collection.

960
01:10:12,400 --> 01:10:13,913
Enough, sir!

961
01:10:14,480 --> 01:10:16,436
We deal with serious things here.

962
01:10:16,640 --> 01:10:18,520
What we do here
determines the lives of children

963
01:10:18,640 --> 01:10:20,720
and the happiness
of families that are now suffering.

964
01:10:20,920 --> 01:10:23,480
I don't fiind your mockery
amusing in the least.

965
01:10:23,680 --> 01:10:27,832
Our plant is bankrupt, madam. They're
privatizing it at the end of the month.

966
01:10:28,040 --> 01:10:29,996
And they want to lay us all off.

967
01:10:30,200 --> 01:10:33,590
Most of the guys you see out there
have children.

968
01:10:33,800 --> 01:10:37,713
Children who want to eat, get dressed,
go to school, play...

969
01:10:38,800 --> 01:10:41,473
How can they do that, madam,
if their fathers are unemployed? How?

970
01:10:43,560 --> 01:10:47,075
- Stop yelling at me. I can't help you.
- Why, doctor, why?

971
01:10:49,160 --> 01:10:52,118
The sperm that we buy here, we sell abroad.

972
01:10:52,400 --> 01:10:55,517
We sell it to families that can't
have children the natural way.

973
01:10:55,800 --> 01:10:57,711
We sell it to gay women

974
01:10:57,920 --> 01:11:00,718
who want to have a child
without a man in their lives.

975
01:11:01,720 --> 01:11:03,790
These people have a lot of money.

976
01:11:04,320 --> 01:11:08,472
Enough money to buy the sperm
and also the treatment that's needed.

977
01:11:08,960 --> 01:11:12,873
They want to give their children
as many chances as possible.

978
01:11:13,160 --> 01:11:14,991
Yes, of course.

979
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:19,109
That's why they want to donor to be
a tall, handsome, young man...

980
01:11:19,360 --> 01:11:24,070
with a high lQ, well-educated
and cultured.

981
01:11:25,320 --> 01:11:27,117
Let me give you an example.

982
01:11:27,320 --> 01:11:30,232
The best seller on the market now is
the sperm of Danish students.

983
01:11:30,440 --> 01:11:32,749
They're tall, handsome, blond.

984
01:11:33,080 --> 01:11:36,277
Our clients do not want to buy
the sperm of a Romanian worker.

985
01:11:36,640 --> 01:11:39,359
Especially not in those quantities.

