1023
01:14:23,920 --> 01:14:26,912
So, Gica, how was it?
Are you fiinished, huh?

1024
01:14:27,400 --> 01:14:29,241
Come on, don't keep us waiting.
Did you donate?

1025
01:14:29,400 --> 01:14:31,630
How was it? It didn't hurt, did it?

1026
01:14:34,400 --> 01:14:37,437
Guys, they don't want to collect.

1027
01:14:39,640 --> 01:14:42,712
What do you mean, they
don't want to collect?

1028
01:14:42,960 --> 01:14:44,791
Why did we come all this way?

1029
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:47,116
What, they don't have enough jars?

1030
01:14:48,200 --> 01:14:51,078
They don't wanna collect
because we' re workers.

1031
01:14:54,560 --> 01:14:56,471
Come on, you scared us.
Now tell us!

1032
01:14:56,920 --> 01:14:59,195
Come on, we're in a hurry.
We can go in 2 or 3 at a time.

1033
01:14:59,400 --> 01:15:01,709
Hey! Didn't you hear?
They're not collecting, damn it!

1034
01:15:05,640 --> 01:15:07,392
Wait, wait!

1035
01:15:08,240 --> 01:15:11,471
- Why is that, Gica? Why?
- Because we're workers.

1036
01:15:11,720 --> 01:15:14,234
- They' re saying their clients...
- Quiet!

1037
01:15:14,440 --> 01:15:16,715
Wait, let's hear what the man has to say.

1038
01:15:17,560 --> 01:15:20,597
They say... their clients don't want
to buy from workers.

1039
01:15:20,800 --> 01:15:22,518
Who do they want to buy from?

1040
01:15:22,720 --> 01:15:26,952
